stylometry:
Trade off: should you have a line for each server and that server just takes the next one in their line (example of that would be a grocery store) or should you have one line and have the next available server take the next person in line ( example of that would be a bank)

You have to take into consideration the number of servers, average customer waiting time, and how many people come into your store per hour. 

 The objective is to find the best possible way to get customers in and out of your store in a quick manner without losing too much money by having too many servers.
